      • DistCustomCategorical

        public DistCustomCategorical(double[] pmf,
                             boolean keepLocked)
        Create an instance where outcomes map to integers 1-K. You may wish to add ranges so that one of a particular set of integers is returned, in which case you should keep the distribution locked until all ranges have been added (and then unlock it).
        Parameters:
        pmf - The probability mass function (PMF) as an array of probabilities.
        keepLocked - Whether to keep the distribution locked (see above).
        Since:
        0.2

        public void unlock()
        Unlock the distribution (allowing it to be sampled) after changes to probabilities are completed. The probabilities will need to sum to 1 at this point.
        Overrides:

      • setProbability

        public void setProbability(C categoryValue,
                           double prob)
        Set (change) a probability value linked to a categorical outcome. The distribution will be locked automatically when you change the first probability; you should unlock it after the last change is done.
        Parameters:
        categoryValue - The enum value (category) being changed.
        prob - The new probability.
        Since:
        0.1

      • setProbability

        public void setProbability(int outcomeNum,
                           double prob)
        Set (change) a probability value linked to a numeric (integer) outcome. The distribution will be locked automatically when you change the first probability; you should unlock it after the last change is done.
        Parameters:
        outcomeNum - The number ('position') of the outcome to change (1-K).
        prob - The new probability.
        Since:
        0.2
